				<div type="general">
					<p xml:space="preserve">Hasköy is a small town in the south of the Eastern Anatolian 
               province Muş, located 35 km from the city of 
               Muș. The town has approximatively 15.000 inhabitants, all of whom speak Arabic as their mother tongue. </p>
					<p xml:space="preserve">Until recently, its inhabitants led a semi-nomadic, pastoral life. </p>
				</div>
				<div type="researchHistory">
					<p xml:space="preserve">Shabo Talay was the first researcher to work on the Arabic dialect of Hasköy. 
               <rs type="bibl" ref="zotid:E629W3I7">Talay (2001)</rs> is a grammatical sketch of the dialect and 
               <rs type="bibl" ref="zotid:FSWQJUUN">Talay (2002)</rs> is a collection of transcribed texts. </p>
				</div>
